        ii.
            Catalytic Cracking is useful to break down longer chain hydrocarbons into shorter chain hydrocarbons. Longer chain hydrocarbons are more common, but shorter chain hydrocarbons have higher demand as they can be better fuels and used more readily to make plastics. Also, they are generally more expensive. Catalytic cracking allows these more abundant long chain hydrocarbons to be broken down into the more expensive shorter chain ones, which can be sold for more profit and in-general are more demanded and more useful.
